I'm always thinking of
different ways to explain it.

00:00:22.300 --> 00:00:24.640
So the things we normally learn
is,

00:00:24.640 --> 00:00:28.270
if you've got some battery
here, some number of volts,

00:00:28.270 --> 00:00:31.974
let's give it the symbol
E, and you have a

00:00:31.974 --> 00:00:36.057
resistor,
we just say there's a 1.5 volt

00:00:36.057 --> 00:00:37.320
difference.
 

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:40.780
So you can say this is 0 this
is 1.5.

00:00:40.780 --> 00:00:44.130
Current goes around and comes
back.

00:00:44.130 --> 00:00:47.447
And we say the work is done,
because the battery is somehow

00:00:47.447 --> 00:00:49.220
making the current go around.
 

00:00:49.220 --> 00:00:52.696
But we look under the hood and
found it's somewhat more

00:00:52.696 --> 00:00:53.340
