00:00:53.340 --> 00:00:58.250
It is not done entirely with
the electrostatic force.

00:00:58.250 --> 00:01:02.405
The electrostatic force is due
to these charges here,

00:01:02.405 --> 00:01:06.402
sitting on the plate,
but they cannot do work for a

00:01:06.402 --> 00:01:09.360
charge that goes round and
round.

00:01:09.360 --> 00:01:12.421
Because if you go round in a
full loop in an electrostatic

00:01:12.421 --> 00:01:14.840
field, the net work done by the
field is 0.

00:01:14.840 --> 00:01:17.531
That's because the net work
done is the integral of the

00:01:17.531 --> 00:01:19.971
electrostatic field and because
it's conservative,

00:01:19.971 --> 00:01:20.819
you'll get 0.
 

00:01:20.819 --> 00:01:23.658
Yet when charges go round and
round the circuit,

00:01:23.658 --> 00:01:27.040
they are doing some work,
because the resistor is heating

00:01:27.040 --> 00:01:28.489
up, delivering heat.
 

00:01:28.489 --> 00:01:32.569
And the hidden secret of course
is not the electrostatic force,

00:01:32.569 --> 00:01:36.519
but another force inside the
battery that's doing the job.

00:01:36.519 --> 00:01:40.010
So I gave an analogy which I
think is worth repeating.

00:01:40.010 --> 00:01:47.110
So here is a ski slope and you
start here and you come down.

00:01:47.110 --> 00:01:52.312
Let's imagine on the way down
you bump into a lot of trees,

00:01:52.312 --> 00:01:56.260
that you pretty much come down
at 0 speed.

00:01:56.260 --> 00:02:00.968
Then you stagger back to the
foot of this ski lift.

00:02:00.968 --> 00:02:04.140
Now that's the end of your
skiing.

00:02:04.140 --> 00:02:07.090
There's nothing else,
because gravity is not going to

00:02:07.090 --> 00:02:09.813
help you anymore,
because gravity is not going to

00:02:09.813 --> 00:02:11.800
help you go from here to there.
 

00:02:11.800 --> 00:02:15.080
So it's not obviously run by
just gravity.

00:02:15.080 --> 00:02:17.870
That's when you have the ski
lift, which I'm going to portray

00:02:17.870 --> 00:02:20.474
as a vertical thing,
where you've got a lot of

00:02:20.474 --> 00:02:24.159
chairs, so you can sit on one of
them and you can ride to the

00:02:24.159 --> 00:02:24.590
top.
 

00:02:24.590 --> 00:02:27.280
So that ski lift exerts a force.
 

00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:30.020
Gravity, which is acting down
here,

00:02:30.020 --> 00:02:32.960
is also acting down here,
and the ski lift,

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:37.140
F_ski and
F_gravity, ski

00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:41.030
lift cancels gravity here and
takes you to the top.

00:02:41.030 --> 00:02:43.126
So if you define the analog of
an emf, there is no

00:02:43.126 --> 00:02:44.710
"electro"
about this one.

00:02:44.710 --> 00:02:46.280
Let's just call it emf.
 

00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:51.220
As the integral of the forces
acting on this one skier,

00:02:51.220 --> 00:02:57.733
as he or she goes around the
loop, you can write that as the

00:02:57.733 --> 00:03:03.694
force due to gravity ⋅
dr and the force due to the

00:03:03.694 --> 00:03:08.949
lift--
or what did I call it?

00:03:08.949 --> 00:03:11.129
Hey guys, you know what this
was called?

00:03:11.129 --> 00:03:12.060
Student:  Ski.
 

00:03:12.060 --> 00:03:12.930
Prof: Ski.
 

00:03:12.930 --> 00:03:16.280
Okay, ski dot dr.
 

00:03:16.280 --> 00:03:19.628
this is no good.
 

00:03:19.628 --> 00:03:22.985
Gravity does something to you
when you come down and takes it

00:03:22.985 --> 00:03:24.438
all back when you go up.
 

00:03:24.438 --> 00:03:28.437
This guy, the force inside the
ski, has a non-zero line

00:03:28.437 --> 00:03:32.508
integral, because it's a
non-zero force only in here.

00:03:32.508 --> 00:03:36.744
The line integral's basically
the ski force times the

00:03:36.744 --> 00:03:37.639
distance.
 

00:03:37.639 --> 00:03:40.419
The ski force is just
mg, the magnitude.

00:03:40.419 --> 00:03:42.128
That times the distance is
mgh.

00:03:42.128 --> 00:03:45.263
That's why you can say this
point is a potential mgh

00:03:45.263 --> 00:03:46.560
