analogy.

00:04:27.028 --> 00:04:29.269
So I'm going to draw it not
this way but this way.

00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:33.185
Here's the top plate and here's
the bottom plate and you may

00:04:33.185 --> 00:04:36.970
directly visualize the height
here to be the potential.

00:04:36.970 --> 00:04:39.920
Then there is a wire that has
no resistance.

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:41.290
It's going to be flat.
 

00:04:41.290 --> 00:04:44.557
Potential doesn't have to be up
or down for current to flow down

00:04:44.557 --> 00:04:44.920
this.
 

00:04:44.920 --> 00:04:47.050
Then here is a resistor.
 

00:04:47.050 --> 00:04:51.379
Then there's another little
wire, which is pretty much flat

00:04:51.379 --> 00:04:53.319
and joins at the bottom.
 

00:04:53.319 --> 00:04:57.028
There are charges piled up
here, there are charged piled up

00:04:57.028 --> 00:04:58.759
here,
and they will produce an

00:04:58.759 --> 00:05:01.350
electrostatic field that will do
something there,

00:05:01.350 --> 00:05:03.588
but inside, they're bad.
 

00:05:03.588 --> 00:05:08.240
Electrostatic field goes down
here.

00:05:08.240 --> 00:05:10.709
So if this is the whole story,
you cannot do anything,

00:05:10.709 --> 00:05:12.560
because maybe if you charged it
once,

00:05:12.560 --> 00:05:14.850
it will go round and come back
here and it's stuck,

00:05:14.850 --> 00:05:16.629
because it cannot go up.
 

00:05:16.629 --> 00:05:20.396
That's when the tiny little
hands of the chemical forces

00:05:20.396 --> 00:05:23.959
will come and drag the charge,
against this field.

00:05:23.959 --> 00:05:27.939
That's the F_chemical
force.

00:05:27.939 --> 00:05:31.680
And it's the line integral of
the chemical force around a

00:05:31.680 --> 00:05:33.819
closed loop that's called emf.
 

00:05:33.819 --> 00:05:38.028
If you write the chemical force
per unit charge,

00:05:38.028 --> 00:05:43.399
integrate over a closed loop,
that's what we call the emf.

00:05:43.399 --> 00:05:44.889
But that's very easily computed.
 

00:05:44.889 --> 00:05:47.425
That's what I didn't realize,
a much easier way to do the

00:05:47.425 --> 00:05:48.060
computation.
 

00:05:48.060 --> 00:05:51.839
This thing is just a product of
that force times the distance,

00:05:51.839 --> 00:05:54.781
but in magnitude,
that force precisely cancels

00:05:54.781 --> 00:05:58.603
the downward electric force,
just like the lift cancels the

00:05:58.603 --> 00:05:59.680
force of gravity.
 

00:05:59.680 --> 00:06:04.274
So the line integral in
magnitude is just the electric

00:06:04.274 --> 00:06:08.348
field times the distance between
the two plates,

00:06:08.348 --> 00:06:11.209
and that is just the voltage.
 

00:06:11.209 --> 00:06:14.673
Therefore the voltage
difference between this point

00:06:14.673 --> 00:06:16.959
and this point will be the emf.
 

00:06:16.959 --> 00:06:18.939
Now if you don't want to know
the whole details,

00:06:18.939 --> 00:06:20.910
